<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Pseudo Class & Pseudo Element Demo</title>

<style>
*{
    margin:0;
    padding:0;
    box-sizing:border-box;
    font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}

body{
    background:#f4f4f4;
}

/* Navigation Bar */
nav{
    background:#2c3e50;
    padding:15px;
    text-align:center;
}

nav a{
    color:white;
    text-decoration:none;
    margin:0 15px;
    padding:10px 15px;
    transition:0.3s;
}

/* Pseudo Class */
nav a:hover{
    background:#e74c3c;
    border-radius:5px;
}

.container{
    width:80%;
    margin:50px auto;
    text-align:center;
}

/* Pseudo Elements */
h1::before{
    content:"👉 ";
    color:blue;
}

h1::after{
    content:" 🔥";
}

p{
    width:70%;
    margin:25px auto;
    font-size:18px;
    line-height:1.7;
    color:#333;
    text-align:justify;
}

/* Pseudo Class */
p:hover{
    color:green;
}

/* Pseudo Elements */
p::first-letter{
    font-size:35px;
    color:red;
    font-weight:bold;
}

p::first-line{
    font-weight:bold;
    color:#0f3c69;
}

button{
    padding:12px 25px;
    background:green;
    color:white;
    border:none;
    border-radius:5px;
    cursor:pointer;
    font-size:16px;
    transition:0.3s;
}

/* Pseudo Class */
button:hover{
    background:red;
}
</style>

</head>
<body>

<nav>
    <a href="#">Home</a>
    <a href="#">About</a>
    <a href="#">Courses</a>
    <a href="#">Services</a>
    <a href="#">Contact</a>
</nav>

<div class="container">

    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>

    <p>
        CSS Pseudo Classes and Pseudo Elements are powerful features that allow
        developers to style elements based on their state or specific parts
        without adding extra HTML. Pseudo Classes like <strong>:hover</strong>
        make web pages interactive, while Pseudo Elements like
        <strong>::before</strong>, <strong>::after</strong>,
        <strong>::first-letter</strong>, and
        <strong>::first-line</strong> help create attractive and creative
        designs with minimal code.
    </p>

    <button>Click Me</button>

</div>

</body>
</html>
